Compilation
===========

In this directory to build the library just type 

    make

It is independent of the other files of Premia; we extracted the complex.h complex.c 
files from src/common/mathtools/ in this directory

It will compile the following model

	1) bermudan swaption pricer by least square method
	2) A stochastic volatility extension of the LMM
	3) Arbitrage free discretization of the LMM

WARNING
=======

1) To build the Non exploding Bushy tree you should go in the subdirectory lmm_bushy/
and read the README file  

2) For Andersen bermudan swaption pricer you should go in the subdirectory lmm_andersen_bermudianswaption and read the README file

3) For LMM with Jump you should go in the subdirectory lmm_jump_glassermanmerenenr/
and read the README file  

4) For LMM-CEV you should go in the subdirectory lmm_cev and read the README file

5) For LMM-EBERLEIN-OZBAN article go in the subdirectory LMM-EBERLEIN-OZBAN-CAPSFLOOR.dir and read the README file

6) For LMM-MODEL-STOCHASTIC-VOLATILITY-ANDERSEN article go in the subdirectory  LIBOR-MARKET-MODEL-STOCHASTIC-VOLATILITY-ANDERSEN.di and read the README file

7) For HJM-LEVY-EBERLEIN-KLUGE article go in the subdirectory HJM-LEVY-EBERLEIN-KLUGE-CAPS-SWAPTIONS.di and read the README file

8)  For Kolodko-Schoenmarkers bermudan swaption pricer you should go in the subdirectory lmm_kolodko_schoenmarkers_bermudianswaption and read the README file

Version
=======

the compilation works under Red Hat 9 with:

	gcc (GCC) 3.2.2 20030222 (Red Hat Linux 3.2.2-5)
	glibc-2.3.2-11.9




